cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with first-order logic with modular predicates and its expressive power. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the characterization of word languages in a specific fragment of first-order logic with modular predicates. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with the decidability of certain fragments of first-order logic with modular predicates. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are less likely categories, but they could be relevant if the paper proposes new algorithms or programming language constructs based on the results obtained.
